11/03/2010
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Security Minister Sadik Ahmetovic and the head of the European Commission (EC) delegation to BiH, Dimitris Kourkoulas, opened a new border checkpoint between BiH and Montenegro on Wednesday (March 10th). 
The EU allocated 2.6m euros for the construction and maintenance of the Klobuk crossing. 
Officials say it should boost border and customs control. 
(RTRS, Srna, BHRT, Nezavisne Novine - 10/03/10)
